"{\"uid\": \"www.theatlantic.com.-politics-archive-2016-06-brexit-right-488684-\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"illusory promise to restore a vision of national greatness that never truly existed in the first place.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is a promise of change, a promise that things will be better once more.\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David Frum has argued that the vote is a reaction against the arrival of 630,000 foreign nationals in 2015 alone, which he terms \\\"the greatest mass migration since perhaps the Anglo-Saxon invasion.\\\"\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And on this side of the Atlantic, 80 percent of Trump supporters in the Republican primary believed immigrants create more burden than benefit.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Western political establishment is inclined to dismiss such reactions as bigotry that should not be dignified with a response.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, they deploy slogans of the status quo: Remain, Stronger Together.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are intended as dark warnings of the costs of change, and intimations that those who vote for it are motivated solely by prejudice and ignorance.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And here is where the failure of imagination proved catastrophic for the established elites.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They failed to paint a vision of a better, brighter future.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They failed to offer a persuasive account of how much their people had gained.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They failed to address the real concerns of their constituents, or to acknowledge that the interests of different constituencies sometimes diverge.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They looked at those who pointed to the flaws in the global consensus-from Bernie Sanders to Nigel Farage-and saw only ideologues making outlandish promises.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They audaciously gambled that by presenting a stark choice, an all-or-nothing vision of globalization, they could persuade their voters to go all in.\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They seem not to have seriously considered that voters would embrace the alternative.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday morning, Britons woke to a plunging pound, a rudderless state, and an unsettled future.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of making Britain great again, the vote threatens to make an end to Great Britain.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scotland and Northern Ireland may break away.\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The economic fallout is only beginning.\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Decades of laws must now be re-written.\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it may be too late for regrets: Britons, Europe says, are stuck with the result for which they voted.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps Britain's parliamentary democracy played a crucial role.\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its voters are accustomed to electing representatives who make stark promises, and then watching as they work out the painful compromises necessary for governance.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This fueled the anger of recent decades, as voters looked on powerlessly as campaign pledges dissolved or picked up ballots devoid of representatives who would accurately reflect their opinions.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cameron gave them the chance to voice directly their own, unmediated views-without the filter of representative democracy to reconcile them with other constraints.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At least a few of those voters are stunned by the result.\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I voted Leave but did not think my vote would count,\\\" one told the BBC.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never thought it would actually happen.\\\"\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, it happened.\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now Americans are left to make sense of it.\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's a great thing that happened,\\\" said Donald Trump.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Good on you for ignoring all the fear mongering from special interest globalists who tend to aim for that apocalyptic One World Government that dissolves a nation's self-determination and sovereignty,\\\" cheered Sarah Palin.\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether Trump produces a similar success in November may depend less on what he does between now and then than the way the political elites he is challenging-in his own party, and on the other side of the aisle-choose to respond.\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Will they display enough empathy to convince angry, hurting voters they understand their pain is real?\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Will they exercise enough imagination to offer a\", \"from\": 35